  .ccLetter
    p.first So,!{' '}
      span there's your syllabus.
      |!{' '}Now, before I get my head down and make this…!{' '}
      span.bold three quick things.
    p.header.thc1 1/ It’s going to be short
    p You know those courses where instructors waffle for ten minutes over some bullet points.
    p.inwardSpeech This is going to be absolutely nothing like that.
    p I want to give you!{' '}
      span.italic as much as possible in as little time as possible.
      |!{' '}New diagrams, examples, templates every 20 seconds.
    //- p There's a lot to cover. And I want to cover it in as few seconds as possible.
    p.header.thc2 2/ It’s going to be simple
    p I started Marketing Examples cause I was fed up of reading 1000 words and leaving with very little.
    p Everything is step-by-step.
    p Simple doesn't mean easy. It means!{' '}
      span.italic eliminating the unnecessary so that the necessary may speak.
    p.header.thc3 3/ It’s going to be practical
    p I'm not teaching the theory of marketing. My!{' '}
      span.italic only
      |!{' '}goal is to give you the practical skills you need to grow businesses. That's it.
    p.inwardSpeech Strategy. Examples.!{' '}
      span.bold Exactly
      |!{' '}how I do it.
    p That's the formula. I want this to be as!{' '}
      span.italic REAL
      |!{' '}as possible.
    //- p I want to get as close to reality as possible.
    //- p That's the format. Marketing!{' '}
    //-   span.italic reality.
    //-   |!{' '}Not marketing!{' '}
    //-   span.italic theory.
    //- p That's my formula. I'm not teaching the theory of marketing.
    p.asterix * * *
    p Alright. That's everything for now. If you'd like to know when this comes out (and get a launch discount) pop your email in the box.
